1
00:00:01,616 --> 00:00:05,791
(seagulls crying)

2
00:00:06,084 --> 00:00:08,797
Wow, amazing!

3
00:00:08,881 --> 00:00:10,927
So many yachts!

4
00:00:11,011 --> 00:00:13,640
I wonder how far
those things can go?

5
00:00:13,724 --> 00:00:16,521
They can go all the way
to foreign countries.

6
00:00:16,605 --> 00:00:18,483
The oceans are all connected,
after all.

7
00:00:18,985 --> 00:00:22,033
I'd love to ride one.
Me too.

8
00:00:22,116 --> 00:00:24,078
Never mind all that.

9
00:00:24,162 --> 00:00:28,754
I'm getting hungry, so let's hurry
back and eat our lunches.

10
00:00:29,088 --> 00:00:33,680
Sigh... I guess for you, Genta,
it's appetite over romance.

11
00:00:35,267 --> 00:00:36,269
Huh?

12
00:00:41,655 --> 00:00:44,243
That looks delicious!

13
00:00:46,790 --> 00:00:48,585
Hey... where are you going?

14
00:00:50,339 --> 00:00:53,470
This is the place.
Mr. Takiguchi?

15
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:58,271
I'm from the Shirakabe Hotel.
I've brought the food you ordered.

16
00:00:58,355 --> 00:00:59,691
A hotel, he says.

17
00:00:59,774 --> 00:01:02,488
No wonder it looks
so delicious.

18
00:01:02,571 --> 00:01:06,956
Hey, no matter how long you stare,
there's none for you. Get lost.

19
00:01:07,039 --> 00:01:10,003
Don't be so mean
to them.

20
00:01:11,840 --> 00:01:14,721
Thanks for your trouble. That was quick.
- Takiguchi Nao (34), president's wife.

21
00:01:14,804 --> 00:01:15,932
(dog barking)

22
00:01:16,015 --> 00:01:18,478
A cute little doggy!

23
00:01:18,562 --> 00:01:20,482
His name is Koro.
Woof!

24
00:01:20,984 --> 00:01:22,946
And what a pretty necklace.

25
00:01:23,865 --> 00:01:28,039
Thank you. But it's just
a cheap acrylic one.

26
00:01:28,875 --> 00:01:31,212
Ma'am, where should I
put the food?

27
00:01:31,296 --> 00:01:34,552
Oh, sorry. Could you carry it
onto the boat for me?

28
00:01:35,220 --> 00:01:36,556
You kids, come along too.

29
00:01:36,639 --> 00:01:37,893
Oh... but...

30
00:01:37,976 --> 00:01:40,063
We couldn't, with strangers...

31
00:01:40,147 --> 00:01:44,197
This hotel's food is delicious.
You'll have some, won't you?

32
00:01:44,655 --> 00:01:48,705
But if we eat, there won't be
enough left for you.

33
00:01:49,207 --> 00:01:50,709
Don't hold back, kids.

34
00:01:51,419 --> 00:01:53,173
We ordered with dinner in mind too...
- Takiguchi Kotaro (55), company president.

35
00:01:53,256 --> 00:01:55,219
so there's more than
we can possibly eat.

36
00:01:55,594 --> 00:01:56,596
Huh?

37
00:01:56,679 --> 00:01:58,725
Then we can really
eat some?

38
00:01:59,060 --> 00:02:02,525
Yes. Just the two of us
felt a bit lonely.

39
00:02:02,608 --> 00:02:04,612
We'd be glad to have you.

40
00:02:04,905 --> 00:02:07,117
Well, if you put it that way,
don't mind if we do...

41
00:02:07,201 --> 00:02:08,871
We'll gladly accept!

42
00:02:09,205 --> 00:02:11,919
Hahaha!
Ufufu!

43
00:02:14,048 --> 00:02:15,759
Blazing sun,
undefeated by the heat,

44
00:02:15,843 --> 00:02:17,513
a slick and stylish
deduction show.

45
00:02:17,596 --> 00:02:20,979
We're all witnesses...
a tycoon dives into the sea.

46
00:02:21,062 --> 00:02:22,439
Seeing through to
the one and only truth.

47
00:02:22,523 --> 00:02:24,443
Looks like a kid,
mind of an adult.

48
00:02:24,527 --> 00:02:27,408
His name is
Detective Conan!

49
00:02:29,288 --> 00:02:34,632
♪~

50
00:04:02,767 --> 00:04:08,779
~♪

51
00:04:11,170 --> 00:04:16,070
"The Man Betrayed by the Sea"

52
00:04:16,712 --> 00:04:19,550
Where the heck
did those guys go?

53
00:04:19,926 --> 00:04:23,516
We came all the way to the beach
and you slept the whole time.

54
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:26,647
Let's look a little more,
and if we can't find them...

55
00:04:26,732 --> 00:04:28,736
let's just eat our lunches.

56
00:04:28,819 --> 00:04:31,073
Do that and they'll
hold a grudge.

57
00:04:31,365 --> 00:04:33,746
They say grudges over
food are the scariest.

58
00:04:33,829 --> 00:04:35,248
Yeah, I guess.

59
00:04:35,917 --> 00:04:39,841
Mm! Can you believe Conan and Ai
are missing out...

60
00:04:39,925 --> 00:04:42,722
on such delicious food?
What a shame.

61
00:04:43,431 --> 00:04:48,399
Don't worry about it. It's their own
fault for sleeping at the beach.

62
00:04:48,650 --> 00:04:50,654
Are your other friends
here too?

63
00:04:50,738 --> 00:04:54,078
Yeah. We're all
really close.

64
00:04:54,411 --> 00:04:57,459
But today Ai said she
didn't want to get a tan.

65
00:04:57,542 --> 00:05:02,344
Oh? An elementary schooler
caring that much about her skin.

66
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:05,600
I look forward to seeing
what a beauty she'll become.

67
00:05:05,685 --> 00:05:08,064
And Conan, even though
he's just a kid...

68
00:05:08,147 --> 00:05:10,485
he reads mystery novels
until morning.

69
00:05:10,568 --> 00:05:12,907
He's a bit too
grown-up for a child.

70
00:05:12,991 --> 00:05:14,451
He's just not cute.

71
00:05:14,535 --> 00:05:16,622
Well, excuse me
for not being cute.

72
00:05:16,999 --> 00:05:18,376
Conan!

73
00:05:18,459 --> 00:05:21,883
So then, that cute girl
must be Ai?

74
00:05:21,967 --> 00:05:25,640
Yes. Sorry I'm not
a beauty yet.

75
00:05:25,975 --> 00:05:29,148
Hahaha! You're plenty
beautiful as you are.

76
00:05:29,231 --> 00:05:32,654
For an elementary schooler,
that is. Ahahaha!

77
00:05:32,989 --> 00:05:35,410
What are you two
doing here?

78
00:05:35,745 --> 00:05:37,749
That's our line.

79
00:05:37,832 --> 00:05:41,422
We came looking for you
to finally eat our lunches.

80
00:05:41,505 --> 00:05:44,721
I feel bad for the mother
who made it for you...

81
00:05:44,804 --> 00:05:47,642
but you can just eat your
lunch on the way home.

82
00:05:47,727 --> 00:05:50,440
You two come over here
and eat with us.

83
00:05:50,523 --> 00:05:53,947
Do it. It's delicious...
this roast beef.

84
00:05:54,031 --> 00:05:56,870
This lobster is amazing too!
Mm.

85
00:05:57,747 --> 00:05:59,876
Oh... okay.

86
00:06:00,920 --> 00:06:04,093
Mitsuhiko, you're eating
too much lobster.

87
00:06:04,176 --> 00:06:05,888
This is a spiny lobster,
I keep telling you.

88
00:06:05,971 --> 00:06:08,894
(everyone laughing)
Huh? It's different?

89
00:06:08,977 --> 00:06:10,438
Dear.
Hm?

90
00:06:10,898 --> 00:06:13,319
The children are
laughing at you.

91
00:06:14,739 --> 00:06:16,785
You two are like newlyweds.

92
00:06:17,119 --> 00:06:20,416
Ha! Well, we did just get
married six months ago.

93
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,544
Whaaat?

94
00:06:22,045 --> 00:06:25,135
And it was my first
marriage too.

95
00:06:25,218 --> 00:06:27,430
I was so busy growing
my company...

96
00:06:27,514 --> 00:06:30,729
that I forgot to get married
until this age. Haha!

97
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:38,119
That's so nice.

98
00:06:38,536 --> 00:06:40,081
Going out to sea
on a boat like this...

99
00:06:40,165 --> 00:06:42,627
and swimming in the beautiful
ocean would be wonderful.

100
00:06:42,712 --> 00:06:44,047
That's impossible.

101
00:06:44,131 --> 00:06:47,554
You can't really swim
yet, Ayumi.

102
00:06:47,637 --> 00:06:50,853
If I had a boat like this at home,
I'd learn to swim in no time.

103
00:06:51,187 --> 00:06:54,861
That's the spirit, Ayumi.
No need to be discouraged.

104
00:06:55,195 --> 00:06:57,742
I couldn't swim either
until this age...

105
00:06:57,825 --> 00:07:00,330
but with special training
I learned how.

106
00:07:00,413 --> 00:07:02,877
Where there's a will,
there's a way.

107
00:07:03,252 --> 00:07:05,632
So you joined a
sports club?

108
00:07:05,716 --> 00:07:09,974
No, I built a new house, so I added
a pool while I was at it.

109
00:07:10,058 --> 00:07:12,145
Oh, let me show you
something nice.

110
00:07:12,229 --> 00:07:13,774
Hm?

111
00:07:16,237 --> 00:07:18,032
You were filming all that?

112
00:07:18,449 --> 00:07:21,413
Stop it. This is
embarrassing.

113
00:07:21,873 --> 00:07:24,544
But by the end,
look...

114
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:28,929
You're right!

115
00:07:29,012 --> 00:07:31,475
You can really swim now.

116
00:07:31,558 --> 00:07:36,945
All right! Let's race to that
breakwater and see who's fastest!

117
00:07:37,445 --> 00:07:40,201
Ayumi, you can use
a float ring.

118
00:07:40,285 --> 00:07:42,622
All right, let's do it.
Oh no you don't.

119
00:07:43,165 --> 00:07:45,545
You just drank wine.

120
00:07:45,628 --> 00:07:47,800
And your blood pressure
is high enough as it is.

121
00:07:47,883 --> 00:07:49,636
You need to rest
a bit first.

122
00:07:49,971 --> 00:07:53,144
Tch. And I was sure
I'd win, too.

123
00:07:53,477 --> 00:07:55,273
(dog barking)

124
00:07:55,606 --> 00:07:56,608
Hm?

125
00:07:58,195 --> 00:07:59,866
How old is Koro?

126
00:08:00,283 --> 00:08:02,245
He just turned one.

127
00:08:02,620 --> 00:08:05,794
Huh? The metal clasp on his
collar is rusted.

128
00:08:05,878 --> 00:08:09,259
Oh, maybe because we walk
him even on rainy days.

129
00:08:10,511 --> 00:08:13,977
Oh! Hey, we should
get going soon.

130
00:08:14,812 --> 00:08:16,648
Oh! I forgot!

131
00:08:17,484 --> 00:08:20,908
Going off and getting yourselves
a feast all on your own...

132
00:08:21,450 --> 00:08:24,539
In times like that, someone
should come let me know.

133
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:29,091
I was so worried I almost
called the police.

134
00:08:29,174 --> 00:08:31,930
Eating while you're angry
is bad for digestion.

135
00:08:33,224 --> 00:08:35,478
All right!
Kyahaha!

136
00:08:36,397 --> 00:08:39,236
Here goes!
Nice shot!

137
00:08:39,319 --> 00:08:40,739
Haha!
Whoa!

138
00:08:40,823 --> 00:08:42,242
Take that!

139
00:08:44,037 --> 00:08:45,248
Huh?

140
00:08:45,707 --> 00:08:50,007
Isn't that boat heading out
Nao and her husband's?

141
00:08:51,176 --> 00:08:52,637
You're right.

142
00:08:52,721 --> 00:08:55,268
Yeah, Nao came out too.

143
00:08:55,351 --> 00:08:57,147
Are they going to swim?

144
00:08:57,230 --> 00:09:00,027
Thanks for earlier, mister!

145
00:09:05,914 --> 00:09:08,753
Let's swim too!
Sure.

146
00:09:08,837 --> 00:09:10,339
Then I'll go get
the float ring...

147
00:09:10,423 --> 00:09:12,594
What is this... that's
not right.

148
00:09:13,304 --> 00:09:15,558
Somebody help... somebody!

149
00:09:15,893 --> 00:09:17,604
This is bad, he's drowning!

150
00:09:17,688 --> 00:09:19,024
Dear!

151
00:09:35,682 --> 00:09:39,356
(ambulance siren)

152
00:09:39,690 --> 00:09:41,485
I'm worried.

153
00:09:41,568 --> 00:09:44,074
I'm not really in the
mood to play anymore.

154
00:09:44,157 --> 00:09:45,159
Yeah.

155
00:09:45,243 --> 00:09:48,123
The sun's still high, but
let's head home today.

156
00:09:48,207 --> 00:09:52,340
We can call the fire department later
to ask about Mr. Takiguchi...

157
00:09:57,685 --> 00:10:01,776
You kids were with
Mr. Takiguchi earlier, right?

158
00:10:01,859 --> 00:10:05,366
I went to collect the dishes,
but no one's on the boat.

159
00:10:05,449 --> 00:10:07,705
Do you know anything?

160
00:10:07,788 --> 00:10:11,044
Oh, then we'll go
get the dishes for you.

161
00:10:15,679 --> 00:10:17,181
(barking)

162
00:10:17,515 --> 00:10:21,565
I see... you couldn't
ride in the ambulance, huh?

163
00:10:23,903 --> 00:10:26,199
We should probably
bring Nao and her husband...

164
00:10:26,283 --> 00:10:28,621
their clothes and things,
shouldn't we?

165
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,585
Yeah, you're right. Hm?

166
00:10:36,345 --> 00:10:38,098
Was it really an accident?

167
00:10:38,892 --> 00:10:41,605
The detailed investigation
is still ahead of us...

168
00:10:41,981 --> 00:10:45,989
but according to witnesses, there's
no doubt he jumped in himself.

169
00:10:46,365 --> 00:10:47,993
I can't believe it.
- Katagiri Ryoichi (48), Takiguchi's secretary.

170
00:10:48,077 --> 00:10:50,999
Isn't it possible someone pushed him in?

171
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,711
The only people on the boat...
- Nagai Keiji (38), Detective.

172
00:10:52,795 --> 00:10:54,674
were him and his wife, just the two of them.

173
00:10:54,757 --> 00:10:55,759
Are you saying...

174
00:10:55,842 --> 00:10:57,512
his wife pushed him in?

175
00:10:57,930 --> 00:11:00,476
That's not what
I'm saying...

176
00:11:00,769 --> 00:11:05,528
The president told us. He nearly drowned
in a river as a child...

177
00:11:05,611 --> 00:11:08,617
and ever since, he was afraid
of water and couldn't swim.

178
00:11:08,702 --> 00:11:12,125
He recently did special training
and learned to swim.

179
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,753
Huh?

180
00:11:13,837 --> 00:11:15,297
And who are you?

181
00:11:16,174 --> 00:11:18,011
Oh... excuse us.

182
00:11:18,095 --> 00:11:22,395
The children got acquainted with
the Takiguchis at the beach.

183
00:11:23,021 --> 00:11:26,570
They said the couple was very kind
to them, so we came by.

184
00:11:26,653 --> 00:11:28,532
We brought their clothes too.

185
00:11:28,615 --> 00:11:30,662
And Koro got left
behind as well.

186
00:11:30,746 --> 00:11:31,789
(barking)

187
00:11:31,873 --> 00:11:34,419
How is Mr. Takiguchi's
condition?

188
00:11:34,712 --> 00:11:39,429
Ah... that's...
this is hard to say...

189
00:11:39,512 --> 00:11:41,809
but he was pronounced
dead a short while ago.

190
00:11:42,811 --> 00:11:44,314
What?

191
00:11:45,357 --> 00:11:48,698
No way... such a nice man,
gone just like that.

192
00:11:48,782 --> 00:11:50,284
I can't believe it.

193
00:11:50,367 --> 00:11:53,081
(crying)

194
00:11:53,582 --> 00:11:54,960
In any case, detective...

195
00:11:55,044 --> 00:11:57,966
please investigate properly
whether it was really an accident.

196
00:11:58,050 --> 00:12:01,640
Even before they married, we kept
telling the president she was...

197
00:12:01,724 --> 00:12:03,853
clearly after his money.

198
00:12:03,937 --> 00:12:07,527
But the president was completely
deceived by that woman...

199
00:12:07,610 --> 00:12:09,531
and it came to this in the end.

200
00:12:10,491 --> 00:12:12,078
Are you saying Nao
did something wrong?

201
00:12:12,161 --> 00:12:15,167
There's no way someone
that nice would do something bad!

202
00:12:15,584 --> 00:12:17,380
H-hey, hey!

203
00:12:17,463 --> 00:12:19,217
I apologize.

204
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:22,181
Are you with Mr. Takiguchi's
company?

205
00:12:22,515 --> 00:12:25,772
Yes. I'm Katagiri,
head of the secretarial office.

206
00:12:25,856 --> 00:12:27,818
You children witnessed
the accident?

207
00:12:27,901 --> 00:12:29,487
Yeah, we saw it!

208
00:12:29,571 --> 00:12:33,078
Mr. Takiguchi drowned
right in front of us.

209
00:12:33,453 --> 00:12:37,838
He waved at us and then
jumped into the sea.

210
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:41,469
I see. Then sorry to
trouble you, but...

211
00:12:41,553 --> 00:12:43,599
would you come to the station
and tell us...

212
00:12:43,683 --> 00:12:46,187
about what happened in detail?
Sure.

213
00:12:46,271 --> 00:12:47,273
Yes.
Okay.

214
00:12:59,854 --> 00:13:01,817
When Mr. Takiguchi
jumped in...

215
00:13:02,151 --> 00:13:04,614
do you know where
his wife was?

216
00:13:04,697 --> 00:13:08,037
She was doing something
a little ways off.

217
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:11,545
Probably clearing away
the lunch dishes.

218
00:13:11,878 --> 00:13:15,678
I see. So that's why she was
slow to notice he was drowning.

219
00:13:15,761 --> 00:13:18,434
(knock)
Come in.

220
00:13:23,277 --> 00:13:24,654
Nao!

221
00:13:27,075 --> 00:13:30,541
Ayumi, thank you for
bringing the clothes.

222
00:13:31,585 --> 00:13:34,757
Oh, Nao, your necklace...

223
00:13:34,841 --> 00:13:37,680
Oh, the chain must have
broken when I...

224
00:13:38,140 --> 00:13:40,978
was saving him, and it
sank into the sea.

225
00:13:43,484 --> 00:13:45,946
I've heard the account
from these children...

226
00:13:46,030 --> 00:13:50,247
and it seems certain your husband
jumped into the sea himself.

227
00:13:50,331 --> 00:13:54,255
It does appear to be safe
to treat this as a tragic accident.

228
00:13:54,881 --> 00:13:56,843
It was my fault.

229
00:13:56,927 --> 00:13:59,265
No matter how well he'd
learned to swim...

230
00:13:59,349 --> 00:14:02,103
if only I'd watched
him a little more carefully.

231
00:14:02,563 --> 00:14:05,068
There's just one more
thing I wanted to ask...

232
00:14:05,152 --> 00:14:06,488
It's that very thing.

233
00:14:06,571 --> 00:14:08,158
Mr. Takiguchi told
his colleagues...

234
00:14:08,242 --> 00:14:10,621
that he couldn't swim,
apparently.

235
00:14:10,704 --> 00:14:14,420
Had he really
learned to swim?

236
00:14:14,504 --> 00:14:17,468
Oh, just show them
that, why don't you.

237
00:14:17,552 --> 00:14:20,641
The practice video.
Oh... right.

238
00:14:21,726 --> 00:14:25,776
This was filmed when he first
practiced at the pool.

239
00:14:26,278 --> 00:14:29,116
The ones I'm in were
filmed by...

240
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:32,038
our housekeeper.
Ha.

241
00:14:32,999 --> 00:14:36,298
And this was filmed
last week.

242
00:14:39,846 --> 00:14:44,062
That's good, keep it up.
Don't stop, now turn.

243
00:14:44,355 --> 00:14:47,528
Mm... mmh...
I see.

244
00:14:47,862 --> 00:14:50,993
He really had learned
to swim.

245
00:14:51,661 --> 00:14:53,415
Huh?
Come here a sec.

246
00:14:53,832 --> 00:14:54,834
Huh?

247
00:14:56,212 --> 00:14:57,548
What is it, Conan?

248
00:14:57,632 --> 00:14:59,636
Can you let me
see the video camera?

249
00:14:59,719 --> 00:15:01,723
Sure, that's fine.

250
00:15:08,904 --> 00:15:12,953
Is there something important
captured in this footage?

251
00:15:13,372 --> 00:15:14,624
You're right.

252
00:15:14,707 --> 00:15:17,254
Yeah, Nao came out too.

253
00:15:18,298 --> 00:15:23,099
Good, the audio's recorded too.
The problem is what comes next.

254
00:15:24,686 --> 00:15:27,608
Let's swim too!
Sure.

255
00:15:27,692 --> 00:15:29,195
Then I'll go get
the float ring...

256
00:15:29,278 --> 00:15:31,866
What is this... that's
not right.

257
00:15:32,159 --> 00:15:35,123
Somebody help... somebody!

258
00:15:35,999 --> 00:15:37,795
Here, right here.

259
00:15:38,755 --> 00:15:40,467
Can you zoom in
more on this?

260
00:15:40,551 --> 00:15:43,097
Sure, but the image
will get grainy.

261
00:15:44,726 --> 00:15:50,612
Somebody help... somebody!
Aah... agh...

262
00:15:55,956 --> 00:15:57,418
Dear!

263
00:15:59,464 --> 00:16:01,049
What's going on here?

264
00:16:01,634 --> 00:16:04,891
From when Nao noticed Kotaro
was drowning...

265
00:16:04,974 --> 00:16:07,563
to when she dove in to save him,
there's a slight gap.

266
00:16:08,022 --> 00:16:12,740
And that cruiser had
a life ring on board...

267
00:16:12,823 --> 00:16:14,827
so why didn't she use it?

268
00:16:15,537 --> 00:16:21,216
And one more thing... what was that
in the practice footage?

269
00:16:22,259 --> 00:16:24,222
Kotaro was actually...

270
00:16:25,097 --> 00:16:26,226
(dog barking)

271
00:16:26,309 --> 00:16:29,190
What are you two
whispering about?

272
00:16:29,273 --> 00:16:31,694
Oh, uh...
Woof!

273
00:16:32,696 --> 00:16:35,661
Huh? The metal clasp on his
collar is rusted.

274
00:16:36,036 --> 00:16:39,669
Oh, maybe because we walk
him even on rainy days.

275
00:16:40,462 --> 00:16:42,216
So that's it.

276
00:16:46,933 --> 00:16:48,186
Well then, everyone...

277
00:16:48,270 --> 00:16:52,278
sorry for the trouble, but
you're free to go home.

278
00:16:52,361 --> 00:16:54,699
We'll see the wife
to the hospital.

279
00:16:55,409 --> 00:16:56,703
Thank you for your time.

280
00:16:56,786 --> 00:16:58,707
Could you wait
a moment?

281
00:16:58,790 --> 00:17:02,256
Huh? Is there something
you'd like to say?

282
00:17:02,339 --> 00:17:04,677
Oh, no, no, haha.

283
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:07,349
This was no
mere accident.

284
00:17:07,433 --> 00:17:09,729
It was a carefully
planned murder.

285
00:17:09,812 --> 00:17:11,232
Huh? What did you say?

286
00:17:11,566 --> 00:17:13,153
Ha!
Huh?

287
00:17:13,612 --> 00:17:17,202
But Mr. Takiguchi jumped
into the sea himself.

288
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:18,788
Yes. However...

289
00:17:18,872 --> 00:17:21,669
if he had known he
couldn't swim...

290
00:17:21,753 --> 00:17:25,177
Mr. Takiguchi never would
have jumped in, would he?

291
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:29,727
Mr. Takiguchi was made to believe
he could swim when he couldn't...

292
00:17:29,810 --> 00:17:31,439
and was suddenly taken
out on the cruiser...

293
00:17:31,522 --> 00:17:34,779
to open water where
his feet couldn't touch.

294
00:17:34,862 --> 00:17:38,161
Isn't that a clear-cut
murder?

295
00:17:38,244 --> 00:17:40,999
Don't you agree,
Nao Takiguchi?

296
00:17:41,292 --> 00:17:46,177
My husband could swim
just fine. You saw it too.

297
00:17:46,552 --> 00:17:49,850
Are you saying there's some
trick in that footage?

298
00:17:50,185 --> 00:17:53,566
No, that footage
is genuine.

299
00:17:53,650 --> 00:17:55,904
Mr. Takiguchi
could swim.

300
00:17:55,988 --> 00:17:58,159
Th-then what on earth
are you saying...

301
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:02,376
But only in
his home pool.

302
00:18:02,459 --> 00:18:03,545
Conan.

303
00:18:03,628 --> 00:18:04,839
Coming!

304
00:18:05,966 --> 00:18:09,390
Here, let me borrow that.
The part from when he was...

305
00:18:09,974 --> 00:18:12,521
practicing his kicks. Look
at Nao's necklace here.

306
00:18:13,273 --> 00:18:16,028
See, it's sunk
in the water, right?

307
00:18:16,111 --> 00:18:20,162
But on the last day...
look, it's floating in the water!

308
00:18:20,245 --> 00:18:22,791
Huh? W-wait a minute.

309
00:18:25,380 --> 00:18:29,638
Y-you're right, the necklace that
was sunk is now floating.

310
00:18:29,722 --> 00:18:33,438
Could you explain what this
means in plain terms?

311
00:18:33,521 --> 00:18:35,567
(throat clearing)

312
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:37,821
Why did the necklace float?

313
00:18:37,905 --> 00:18:39,909
Koro is what told me.

314
00:18:40,786 --> 00:18:45,378
Koro, who supposedly
just turned one...

315
00:18:45,462 --> 00:18:48,050
yet the metal clasp on his
collar has somehow rusted.

316
00:18:48,133 --> 00:18:52,810
The wife put a large amount
of bath salts in the pool water...

317
00:18:52,893 --> 00:18:55,774
to make the body float
more easily.

318
00:18:55,857 --> 00:18:59,030
The necklace in the footage
is made of acrylic.

319
00:18:59,114 --> 00:19:04,291
Acrylic has a specific density of
about 1.17 to 1.2...

320
00:19:04,375 --> 00:19:09,927
so last week's pool water must
have had a higher density than that.

321
00:19:10,010 --> 00:19:13,100
Isn't that right, ma'am?

322
00:19:13,184 --> 00:19:14,311
You're wrong.

323
00:19:14,395 --> 00:19:18,903
If I'd put in that many bath salts,
even my oblivious husband would notice.

324
00:19:18,987 --> 00:19:20,991
Then what did you put in?

325
00:19:21,074 --> 00:19:24,957
The necklace that sank in the sea
floats in the footage.

326
00:19:25,667 --> 00:19:27,963
Either way, this footage...

327
00:19:28,046 --> 00:19:31,888
proves the pool water's
density was high.

328
00:19:32,222 --> 00:19:35,770
Shall we head to your
home now and check?

329
00:19:35,854 --> 00:19:37,900
Even if you go,
there's no water.

330
00:19:37,983 --> 00:19:40,864
I've already drained
the pool.

331
00:19:40,947 --> 00:19:43,286
Don't underestimate
the police.

332
00:19:43,369 --> 00:19:45,790
If there's even a bit
of residue in the pool...

333
00:19:45,874 --> 00:19:49,340
we'll know exactly what
was dissolved in it.

334
00:19:50,759 --> 00:19:54,266
Ma'am, is what
this man is saying true?

335
00:19:55,059 --> 00:19:56,437
Well?

336
00:19:58,233 --> 00:20:00,110
Nao, it's not
true, right?

337
00:20:03,075 --> 00:20:05,120
It's true...

338
00:20:05,413 --> 00:20:06,874
Huh...?

339
00:20:07,292 --> 00:20:11,801
Just as he says, at first
I put in bath salts...

340
00:20:12,093 --> 00:20:16,101
but when I increased the amount,
he noticed.

341
00:20:16,602 --> 00:20:19,358
So after that I switched to
a water-soluble polymer.

342
00:20:20,025 --> 00:20:23,366
A harmless substance used
in medicine and food.

343
00:20:24,243 --> 00:20:27,624
Last week's pool water
probably had a density...

344
00:20:27,708 --> 00:20:30,087
over 1.3, I'd guess.

345
00:20:31,257 --> 00:20:32,884
1.3, you say...

346
00:20:32,968 --> 00:20:36,475
that's about the same as the Dead Sea,
where you can float and read a book.

347
00:20:37,602 --> 00:20:40,984
No wonder Mr. Takiguchi
mistakenly believed...

348
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:42,654
that he could swim.

349
00:20:43,573 --> 00:20:47,414
You filmed the video thinking
it would help you...

350
00:20:47,497 --> 00:20:49,918
when the police came
asking questions.

351
00:20:50,253 --> 00:20:53,968
But that footage turned out
to be your undoing.

352
00:20:56,265 --> 00:20:57,893
That man...

353
00:20:57,976 --> 00:21:01,734
all he ever thought about
was growing his company.

354
00:21:02,652 --> 00:21:07,204
For that, he'd use any dirty
trick without a second thought.

355
00:21:07,788 --> 00:21:11,545
Never knowing how many people
he'd ruined because of it.

356
00:21:11,629 --> 00:21:16,054
So I thought this time
I'd make him suffer...

357
00:21:16,806 --> 00:21:20,563
but living with a man with no
common sense or refinement...

358
00:21:20,647 --> 00:21:22,859
was unbearable agony.

359
00:21:23,694 --> 00:21:27,536
I was at the end
of my patience.

360
00:21:28,246 --> 00:21:32,462
It's true that Mr. Takiguchi was
desperate to make money...

361
00:21:32,546 --> 00:21:35,802
and may have lacked common
sense and refinement.

362
00:21:35,885 --> 00:21:39,143
But compared to you, who killed
a man for revenge...

363
00:21:39,226 --> 00:21:42,441
wasn't he far more
human?

364
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:52,252
♪~

365
00:23:00,221 --> 00:23:05,732
~♪

366
00:23:11,410 --> 00:23:14,374
And I believed she
was such a kind person.

367
00:23:14,958 --> 00:23:18,883
When she treated us to the feast,
I really thought she was nice.

368
00:23:18,966 --> 00:23:21,555
I'm never gonna
trust adults again.

369
00:23:22,097 --> 00:23:25,355
There are all kinds of
adults, you know. All kinds.

370
00:23:25,438 --> 00:23:29,404
That's right. I still have
a pure heart.

371
00:23:29,488 --> 00:23:30,782
Hahaha!
What?

372
00:23:30,865 --> 00:23:32,160
Did you just laugh
purely at me?

373
00:23:32,243 --> 00:23:34,456
Come to think of it, didn't we
still have our lunches?

374
00:23:34,790 --> 00:23:35,958
That's right!

375
00:23:36,042 --> 00:23:38,923
We got treated to lunch, so
our boxes are still here!

376
00:23:39,006 --> 00:23:40,468
Let's hurry and eat!

377
00:23:40,843 --> 00:23:43,557
Now that you mention it,
I'm getting hungry.

378
00:23:43,641 --> 00:23:45,978
I wonder what's in
today's lunch.

379
00:23:46,689 --> 00:23:51,240
Hey, hey, what happened to all
that gloom from just a moment ago?

380
00:23:51,699 --> 00:23:54,538
He's right! Tai-chan's
holding something.

381
00:23:54,871 --> 00:23:57,836
This cat belongs to
my granddaughter.

382
00:23:58,796 --> 00:24:02,094
When these people showed up,
each claimed to be the owner.

383
00:24:02,429 --> 00:24:05,393
No, the real owner
is me, and...

384
00:24:05,476 --> 00:24:07,981
Wrong! I keep telling you,
it's mine!

385
00:24:08,524 --> 00:24:10,486
That's just not
normal.

386
00:24:11,238 --> 00:24:13,826
With a mystery-solving
expert joining in.

387
00:24:15,754 --> 00:24:17,054
Next Conan,

388
00:24:17,054 --> 00:24:21,054
"Lucky Calico Cat Case (Part 1)".

389
00:24:36,854 --> 00:24:39,554
Next Conan's Hint:

390
00:24:39,554 --> 00:24:41,054
"Taii"

391
00:24:41,398 --> 00:24:43,734
The detective team has nothing left to fear.

392
00:24:43,901 --> 00:24:45,005
Or is that really true?

393
00:24:45,100 --> 00:24:47,000
I'm sure there is something.
